, pp. 3004-3032; Ruosteenoja, K., Tuomenvirta, H., Jylhä, K., GCM-based regional temperature and precipitation change estimates for Europe under four SRES scenarios applying a super-ensemble pattern-scaling method (2007) Clim Change, 81, pp. 193-208; Santer, B.D., Wigley, T.M.L., Schlesinger, M.E., Mitchell, J.F.B., (1990) Developing Climate Scenarios From Equilibrium Gcm Results, , Max-Planck-Institut für Meteorologie, Report No 47; Schlesinger, M.E., (1997) Geographical Scenarios of Greenhouse-gas and Anthropogenic-sulfate-aerosol Induced Climate Changes, , Report of the Climate Research Group, Department of Atmospheric Sciences, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign; Sugi, M., Yoshimura, J., Mechanism of tropical precipitation change due to CO2 increase (2004) J Clim, 17, pp. 238-243; Takahashi, K., Matsuoka, Y., Harasawa, H., Impacts of climate change on water resources, crop production and natural ecosystem in the Asia and Pacific region (1998) J Global Environ Eng, 4, pp. 91-103; Vecchi, G.A., Soden, B.J., Global warming and the weakening of the tropical circulation (2007) J Clim, 20, pp. 4316-4340; Wentz, F.J., Ricciardulli, L., Hilburn, K., Mears, C., How much more rain will global warming bring (2007) Science, 317, pp. 233-235; Yang, F., Kumar, A., Schlesinger, M.E., Wang, W., Intensity of hydrological cycles in warmer climates (2003) J Clim, 16, pp. 2419-2423","Shiogama, H.; National Institute for Environmental Studies, 16-2 Onogawa, Tsukuba, Ibaraki 305-8506, Japan; email: shiogama.hideo@nies.go.jp",,,,,,,,01650009,,CLCHD,,"English","Clim. Change",Letter,Scopus,2-s2.0-77149176608
